## üåê Deployment Options

### Option 1: Static Hosting (Free)

#### Netlify (Recommended)
```bash
# Install Netlify CLI
npm install -g netlify-cli

# Login
netlify login

# Deploy
cd sesmine-website
netlify deploy --prod
```

#### Vercel
```bash
# Install Vercel CLI
npm install -g vercel

# Deploy
cd sesmine-website
vercel --prod
```

#### GitHub Pages
1. Create GitHub repository
2. Push code: `git push origin main`
3. Enable Pages in repository settings
4. Access: `username.github.io/repo-name`

### Option 2: Traditional Web Hosting

#### Via FTP
1. Connect using FileZilla or similar
2. Navigate to `public_html` or `www`
3. Upload all files
4. Set permissions: 644 (files), 755 (folders)

#### Via cPanel
1. Login to cPanel
2. Open File Manager
3. Upload ZIP file
4. Extract files
5. Move to public_html

### Option 3: Cloud Platforms

#### AWS S3
```bash
aws s3 sync sesmine-website/ s3://your-bucket/ --acl public-read
aws s3 website s3://your-bucket/ --index-document index.html
```

#### Google Cloud Storage
```bash
gsutil -m cp -r sesmine-website/* gs://your-bucket/
gsutil iam ch allUsers:objectViewer gs://your-bucket
```

